               <head>Mughal copper land grant</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Aurangzeb, Emperor of Hindustan, 1618-1707</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115922" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15497-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176955.0x000001 viaf_6178410" type="supplied">Aurangzeb, Emperor of Hindustan, 1618-1707</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176955.0x000001 viaf_6178410" type="supplied">اورنگ زيب</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>A copper plate in Persian issued in the name of Aurangzeb recording a land grant of 525 bīghah of land in the pargana of Minda (?), suba of Ajmer upon Naẓar ‘Alī Shāh, whose want
                of means of subsistence has left him indigent, on the understanding that he will pray for the perpetuation of his sovereign's rule.</p>
                        <p>Dated 11 Rabīʻ II regnal year [1]4 (AH 1082, 17 August 1671).</p>
                     </note>
